    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-28T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-28T09:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">783.003/139: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-28T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 28, 1936—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 28—11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>78. I learn unofficially that the Capitulations Conference will be held April 19
                    at Montreux, Switzerland. It is expected that we shall receive detailed
                    proposals not later than the end of January.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
